race.comment: ANNOTATE (2) missed a whisker at Albury first-up over 1175m and he's sure to improve. 1400m is his sweet spot and he's well placed with the 3kg claim in easier grade. CHILLI REAPER (9) was beaten a whisker at Donald and it was a tough effort after settling back. She peaks and also rates well enough to fight out the finish. TIERRA (6) was an easy winner at Kilmore and then just missed at Kyneton. Comes back to 1400m off a freshen and has been kept up to the mark with a jumpout win at Avoca. Has a 3kg claim and it's hard to risk the stable. OLLANDIA BEACH (1) is an improving galloper who draws inside again. The win in this grade at Kyneton was good and he keeps the 2k claim.
